node.text:
I answered some questions a while back, in collaboration with @ultrahuman_official, on how motherhood has changed my life for the better! What a wild and epic ride we’re all on! Enjoy 😊 

Check the link in my bio for an exciting offer on the Ultrahuman app.

#Motherhood #Mothersday #Mentalstrength #endurance #strength #fitness #fit #crossfit #fittestmum #Ultrahuman #IAmUltrahuman #fitnessgoals #fitnessmotivation

node.text:
I’ll never be here to tell anyone how to do anything. I’m here making mistakes and correcting them, and then sharing my story with anyone listening. If we all shared experiences rather than pushed opinions and agendas, or in the name of fame and recognition, imagine how far we could all grow together 🥰 New mummas in all your postpartum glory, you’re badass, don’t ever think otherwise!! That kid looking up at you thinks you’re the entire world. 

Happy Monday ✌🏽

Posted @withregram • @crossfitgames An Encouraging Message to New Mothers From 2017 Second-Fittest Woman on Earth @karasaundo 🇦🇺 🔊

Eight-time CrossFit Games athlete and mother Kara Saunders shares what she’d do differently in the postpartum period if she were to do it all over again. Saunders emphasizes recovery, nutrition, and consistency as important things to focus on. 

Saunders finished eighth at the 2020 CrossFit Games. This year, she finished third worldwide in the CrossFit Open and took second in Oceania during the Quarterfinal this past weekend. 

Visit Saunders’ YouTube page to follow her journey through motherhood and fitness.
—
#CrossFitGames #CrossFitMum #Fitness #CrossFit #Workout #CrossFitTraining #CrossFitKids #Inspiration #CrossFitWomen 🎥 @wykieetsebeth

Happy New Year to you all ✌🏽

node.text:
You know things are getting weird when it seems acceptable to overhead squat a chair 🥴🤷🏽‍♀️😂

Half way WOD:

7 Rounds 
40 @rxsmartgearaus drag rope double unders 
7 Double push up wall walks
14 Chair overhead squats

Finished with some bent over backpack rows just because, and a bowl of berries and @atpscience collagen iced coffee. Its the little things in here 🙌🏽

node.text: I workout at the same time everyday to keep a routine and keep the day flowing. I chose to not get any equipment because I’m only moving for wellness, and it’s refreshing to just use good old fashioned body weight movements for my 14 days💪🏽 Movement makes everything a little better 🙌🏽

I’ve been a bit unlucky but I sure did hit the jackpot with this kid 😍☀️ Don’t wanna be greedy 😜

I don’t like to wish any of my life away but I’m counting down the days, baby girl!

node.text:
The easiest way to dedicate a little bit of time to yourself and your body everyday. There is nothing but good that comes from a daily flow ❤️

P.s. find me a facial expression of someone trying to keep it positive more than me in this pic 😂 

Repost @romwod She's not a regular mum, she's a cool mum 🇦🇺🏋🏽‍♀️

We asked #teamromwod athlete, @KaraSaunders her thoughts on ROMWOD's programming and here's what she said...

"You definitely do not need to be an elite athlete to do ROMWOD. If you’re looking to just move better, feel better, and get more out of your training; be pain-free and just generally progress forward and feel better each day then ROMWOD is for you."

node.text:
I just wanted to say THANK YOU! To everyone who has taken time out of their own busy days to check in and make sure I’m ok or to reassure me that everything will in fact be ok! Don’t stop doing that for people, don’t stop being kind to people because it goes a long way and the world needs that right now. That’s all ❤️

📸 @beyond.the.script

node.text:
I’ll always show up. In all of the discomfort and the adversity, I’ll show up and try anyway.

I’m not often proud of myself, but there’s one thing I’ll forever be proud of…I knew I was going to humiliate myself, I knew I wasn’t ok and I was going to come last, I knew I was going to step out in front of everyone and not be able to show how hard I’ve worked, but I pushed my pride aside and I tried anyway. I wasn’t embarrassed or ashamed, I just gave whatever I had to offer. For that I’m proud, and for that growth it was worth it. 

It’s not glamorous and doesn’t come with a medal, but I’ll tell my baby girl one day and hopefully it will give her the courage to always try no matter what ❤️

📸 @furyphotography @inov8training

node.text:
I gave it a nudge but it wasn’t to be. My health 100% comes first and after attempting a day of competition I realised that all it was doing was sending me backwards while my body is still trying to heal.

As always I sacrificed so much to be here, even more so this year by leaving my baby girl for 5 weeks. I’ve cried every single day since I left, got sick in transit, and I’m now withdrawing from the @crossfitgames after all of that. 

It’s been an emotional rollercoaster ride to say the least, but honestly, shit just happens. So many people have lost everything to this pandemic and I just didn’t get to compete, so I still consider myself pretty lucky. 

Thank you to the medical and support crew for having my back and giving me the opportunity to compete, and my sponsors for supporting me through it all. And thank you to everyone for sending me such kind messages always. 

Good luck to all the fierce ladies throwing down this year, enjoy every second! 

❤️

📸 @furyphotography @inov8training

node.text:
I keep thinking of all the amazing things I have back home waiting for me, to get me through this solo trip.

This Shipping container pool is on the way to my new house and I couldn’t be more excited! It’s definitely a little more appealing than the lake here in Madison 😂

6 days until I head home and then 14 days of quarantine and I’ll be sitting in the magnesium pool recovering from this hectic trip! 🙌🏽🙌🏽🙌🏽

Watch this space because I’ll be posting all about it when I’m home 😜

node.text:
I’ve said it before and I’ll say it again, when God blessed me with these legs he had no intention of me walking around doing stupid shit on my hands! 😂
My favourite thing to do when I’m failing my way to success is laugh about it. I cry sometimes too but laughing is much more enjoyable and productive 👊🏽 
Road trippin with @dan_bailey9 to Madison today! Keen to hit that next checkpoint, get some work done and then hustle right back home with my loves.

P.S. The DM’s I’ve gotten have been so helpful and I’m eternally grateful for the kindness people have shared. I can’t reply to all but I see them and I use them. Kindness works, so thank you from the bottom of my heart. ❤️

📸 @michaelpatrickstudio at @crossfitgrandview (Thanks for having me)
